# Line-ending policy. The Copilot generators (scripts/sync-copilot.sh / .ps1) must read identical
# source bytes on every OS — CRLF in the .claude/ sources breaks the Bash frontmatter parser (it keeps
# the trailing \r, so the `--- ` fence never matches and frontmatter is copied untranslated). Force LF
# for the text the fleet is authored in so both generators produce equivalent output. The Bash script
# also strips \r defensively for already-CRLF working copies.
*.md   text eol=lf
*.py   text eol=lf
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.ps1  text eol=lf
*.yml  text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
